snippet.textDisplay: Elon Musk, If you really want 1000 starships in 4 years there is only 1 way to do it AND IT'S NOT RING SECTIONS! You build a machine that accepts the rolls of stainless steel on a 45 degree bias to a welding mandrel the size of what you want to build. snippet.textDisplay: Hey I've been going over some numbers and you might want to put this in front of Elon and all of your techs that are welding. I don't have a way to send you guys data but I can tell you after about the fifth watch of the Starship your going to see a lot of blowouts on your cryo tanks for oxygen/ methane. In the welding process was stainless steel that needs to be cryogenically frozen and then plasma welded and then cryo cooled immediately. Anytime you're working with stainless understand the stainless is a porous material it's heavier than aluminum but it is still porous. Over long periods of time steel becomes brittle under cold temperatures and can withstand massive amounts of heat but then becomes brittle with cold temperatures you must bring the metal to cryo genetic temperatures before welding once the metal reaches cryo temperature immediately plasma fuse the metal and as the welder is moving away from the seams that are welded immediately cryofreeze the seams this will strengthen the seams of the welds and make them stronger. If you do not do this you will have more issues with tanks blowing out. They won't last you but about five to seven missions before you're going to have to junk an entire Starship. The only thing would be salvageable would be the nose cone and some of the engine parts and your fins and Areolons and your header tanks. That's all that will be salvageable from all those ships cryo weld your seams
